Food for obese children: No breakfast and sausage for dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 weigh more than normal; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% are obese.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families leading an unhealthy lifestyle.
We again see the importance of the environment and the behavioral patterns that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children of normal weight.
More than 19% of obese children ate french fries for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is no accident.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not play sports. This, however, applies to most families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time to play sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of the last academic year and involved nearly 900 primary school students across Bohemia.
Obesity is not an accident held for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company Vesobn<0xC3><0xA1> zdravn<0xC3><0xAD> poji<0xC5><0xA1>t'ovna and Unilever.
To date, more than 12,000 schoolchildren from 4 to 8 grades have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient exercise are the main determinants that cause a rapidly growing number of children who suffer from either overweight or obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said they ate five times a day, according to the breakfast-snack-lunch-snack-dinner scheme, and this is one of the prerequisites for proper nutrition,” the study concluded.
No lunch and no sausage in the evening.
Experts warn that even such relative details as the constant time of family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families eat breakfast together.
Most families eat breakfast separately.
The worst discovery is that in one in ten families, people don’t eat breakfast at all.
And yet, breakfast is the basis of the correct daily diet.
The study found that fried food is more often consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet refreshments every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children regularly exercise, this figure is more than halved – up to 15% – when it comes to their parents.
Make your own menu.
In another part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their tastes and preferences.
"Food preferences in Czech children aged 12-15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy eating."
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
“A particular concern is the high popularity of sugary soft drinks,” the study concluded.
As the main dinner, the pasta defeated the bird with a slight advantage.
However, the children showed little interest in legumes, fish and vegetable dishes.
Striving for a healthy lifestyle
The study also found that children were willing to change their eating habits, provided they were provided with relevant information.
"Many participants in the control group of the study demonstrated a significant shift in preferences towards healthy eating when they filled out a questionnaire after the end of the lecture Obesity is not an accident," the project concluded.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet soft drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
In addition, as the main dish, children more often noted birds and fish, limiting the number of sweet dishes and pastries.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article about training for stylists, I lamented the amount of information at the introductory classes.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three experts in the field; tips on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a workshop on how it all works in real life.
Further - more.
The closer we get to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training takes place every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there is not a single man in the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, another has a boyish figure without proper shapes, another weighs more than normal.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce the wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or add the missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of women like Jennifer Lopez, i.e., owners of a lush chest and thighs and a narrow waist, and not to dress them too challenging.
For example, if the difference in the volume of the waist and hips is so large that it is impossible to pick up a skirt or pants, it is worth having at least one thing sewn to order.
You will clearly not regret the invested funds, as perfectly sitting clothes are invaluable.
In a skirt, sewn to order, you will feel much better than in the one that constantly moves, rolls, strips the waist, etc.
Owners of boyish figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruffles, applique, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and types of figures, I am glad that I have a whole week to realize all this.
And yet, I'm afraid, that's too much, given the homework we've been given.
Each participant of the course had to come up with two outfits for a celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I'm going to dress Miranda Kerr, who you may know about Victoria's Secret's advertising campaigns.
I am happy for myself, because it is much easier to dress her than, say, Britney Spears, Christine Aguilera, who has recently recovered by a ton (please bear in mind that I am exaggerating), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We need to cut clothes out of magazines or find them online, print and process them using graphical programs.
The Moodboard - the so-called result of the work - then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep the graphic component of the style in mind.
Stylist not only dresses real people, but creates food pages in magazines (based on special instructions, for example, fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what stylist and designer Mario Kamenik told us.
But it was only on Sunday.
The stylist needs general knowledge
The Saturday lecture, full of information about the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Submissive; fashion designer, Jakub Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Rench.
Yakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should use this fact.
A good stylist can use one item of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn in the usual way, over jeans and a T-shirt like a coat; but it can also be worn on a bare body, without zippers, like a dress.
Another option is to roll up the sleeves or lift the collar, and the whole image changes completely.
“Play with him,” he said.
However, I most appreciated the following advice: "For your work, you need to know the rules perfectly."
Then you can start breaking them,” Jacob told us.
Here I finally understood why we’re going to go through all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see something completely different.
Not to mention fashion shows.
From Ben, the photographer, I learned that the stylist should have more outfit options than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a fashion review of ten pages (equivalent to ten outfits) I must be ready to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that the item of clothing in the picture often looks and works in combination with others is not at all like in reality.
We have to keep this in mind when we create an image.
Honza Pokorny confirmed that often image and style is half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have striking vocals, but her image and marketing have turned her into a world star.
The attitude to the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often consider it superfluous (and believe that it is enough to be an expert in something, and how they look - a second time).
And if someone finally lets us create their style, we should expect them to call us a different (less) size than the one they actually wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids wrote anything about some celebrity getting fat/lost, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it was not enough for a stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up an outfit.
Our job is basically to communicate with the people we dress; that’s why it’s important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to evaluate people, not to condone them and stick to their opinion.
“If a manager asks you to look through her clothes and add a few beautiful things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are terrible.”
“Find at least a few things you can praise and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us what specifically should fit a work bag.
This is a bag that you tie around your waist to carry everything you need.
In addition to the obvious things such as scissors, sticky roller or English pins, it should have a nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting some items, such as bags or hats), special clips to fasten the fabric on the back in case the clothes are too large (bulls and similar items are prohibited because they spoil the clothes) or a set for a seam.
In order to distract from the lectures and gain some practical experience, we learned how to properly make linings on the soles of shoes.
Even when filming in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged — not to mention outdoors.
And here we are, sticking.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors so as not to spoil them.
It requires real skill.
I was glad that Mario praised my work.
These skills did not appeal to me.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m starting to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t that easy, no matter what you say.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Revision
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning trip to work because of a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
The ambitions were satisfied to a certain extent, but this is not important, since no one clearly wanted to do extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subheading "Escape" was associated with great hopes.
It was expected to move the previous series of Need For Speed in a new direction; demo versions indicated that the game will take a worthy place in the genre of racing games.
We were curious to see parts of the game where the protagonist gets out of the car and runs.
As is often the case with NFS, in the end, a lot is different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty good arcade race, but the overall impression is spoiled by a few unnecessary mistakes that have been present in this series of games for several years.
So, in fact, this is not a mistake, but a manifestation of an inexplicable laziness of developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You become part of a story whose protagonist, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has some interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race takes place on its own route, individual stages take place in a diverse and interesting environment.
There is no sense in the game that the same thing happens all the time.
Despite the fact that the graphics are at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are nice to look at.
However, the game does not cause strong emotions.
Although driving through the desert, through the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race from time to time revives an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert, you get into a sandstorm that significantly reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to get under the avalanche.
The individual races are well organized.
There are only a few varieties, but that’s enough.
For a while you try to overtake several opponents (essentially a regular race); then you try to improve the time (standard race with a stopwatch); or you compete against one opponent.
Among other things, you occasionally run into the police, which further complicates your task.
The components on the outside of the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
It's nothing complicated.
Although it is surprising that these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (only three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out that it’s good for the game because it doesn’t bore you; given all of the above, it’s one of the things that makes the game more entertaining.
The racing model follows in the footsteps of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you’re looking for an imitation of real life, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
And yet this driving model is very suitable for dynamic racing, although there are better options on the market.
It's all very well so far.
However, after a while, the problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
From such a game you do not expect complex transformations and collisions, but if you have no idea before the collision with the object, how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, by overtaking or passing cars in a dense flow, you sometimes slightly touch another car. And yet sometimes in a practically similar situation, your car begins to swirl furiously.
Or it's broken.
It’s not so important thanks to the reboot system, but it’s enough to ruin the fun.
Restarts are arranged so that if you crash or leave the track far away, the game takes you back to the point where it was interrupted.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful if something is not working out, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes restarts are not enough, and you have to memorize a separate section of the race.
An important drawback of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to be done in a certain way, otherwise you just don’t fit in.
In other cases, you meet civilian cars in a certain place in the same configuration, regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see your opponent easily passing between two cars moving in the opposite direction, whereas when you get there, the cars are already positioned so that you need to either go around them or drop the speed.
It doesn’t matter when you’re near them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens right in front of your nose.
Competitors have other advantages.
During the game you discover several places where, regardless of the time, the same opponent overtakes you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you drive in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent must stand before you no matter what.
The fact is that when he drives in front of you, he worsens your vision, which leads to one or more accidents in that area.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and filled with adrenaline, but it is so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
It’s a shame, because despite the simple driving model, the game is entertaining and sometimes so full of events that you don’t have time to pay attention to what’s going on around you.
It doesn’t matter what doesn’t make you miss – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to keep track of gas stations along the way, as they are where your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The machines are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars are suitable for straight sections of the highway; and exotic super-sportsmen for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain trails.
The main story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; these are races on individual sites that you will learn during the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points common to the challenges and story modes.
Many opportunities are available to get a higher level of driving: ranging from cars to profile data.
In addition, the profile is associated with the online Autolog feature, which, among other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here’s another flaw that’s hard to understand; it’s an example from the last race in sequence.
You and your car get into a subway tunnel (let’s assume so), where you race the tracks in the dark (let’s assume so).
Your speedometer shows the numbers from 150 to 200 km/h (let’s assume so) when a subway train suddenly hits you from behind, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
For several days, our editors have been discussing whether, when creating the game, no one really thought for a second, or whether its creators really consider us such fools.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video series is mostly pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is a pity that at some critical moments the quality of the recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This is especially true of incidents with a large number of participants, where a good record would not help you much either.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
In order to please the widest possible youth audience, the soundtrack "included compositions from different styles"; but it is unlikely that many people will buy the game because of its music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: Escape is quite messy.
If the game avoided clearly unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of NFS in the last few years.
In any case, the game leaves a feeling of incompleteness.
Of course, this is a good entertainment, but be prepared for the fact that the flaws will blind you as an airport spotlight.
