Fujimori was again hospitalized for medical examination
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized Tuesday at a state hospital for examination for loss of muscle strength seen in his legs, his family doctor said.
Fujimori, 72, who was sentenced to 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed during his reign (1990-2000), suffers from several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, for which he was operated on four times and is under surveillance.
