Aginaga said that in his opinion, Fujimori should be a candidate for the benefit of pardon for humanitarian reasons; however, he said that he did not want it because he knew he was innocent.
He underwent four operations for tongue cancer, lost 18 kilograms, to which other diseases, such as severe erosive gastritis, pancreatic cysts, kidney stones, high blood pressure and problems with blood circulation in the legs, the doctor listed.
Fujimori has been in prison since September 2007, with the Police National Directorate of Special Operations.
